The paper discusses the use of predicate-based communication to simplify programming of autonomous and adaptive systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also introduces a stochastically timed extension of a software component ensemble language, which falls under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper discusses the modeling of a bike sharing system, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses formal semantics and options for design, which falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of predicate-based communication for autonomic computing, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
